{
  "_metadata": {
    "model": "claude-fable-5",
    "cost_usd": 0.34711249999999993,
    "duration_s": 94.121
  },
  "tool_calls": [
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "pwd && ls stm32-project.jsonc 2>/dev/null && cat stm32-project.jsonc 2>/dev/null || echo \"no descriptor in cwd\"",
        "description": "Check cwd for stm32-project.jsonc descriptor"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "stm32 debug read-memory --address 0xE000ED08 --size 4",
        "description": "Read SCB->VTOR (vector table base) on target"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "arm-none-eabi-nm Projects/NUCLEO-L476RG/Examples/GPIO/BLINKY/STM32CubeIDE/Debug/BLINKY.elf | grep -E \"USART2_IRQHandler|Default_Handler|Infinite_Loop\"",
        "description": "List USART2/default handler symbols in the ELF"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "stm32 prog list-probes",
        "description": "List attached ST-LINK probes"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "STM32_PROGRAMMER_DEFAULT_SN=066DFF485754727567021514 stm32 debug read-memory --address 0xE000ED08 --size 4",
        "description": "Read SCB->VTOR via the L476RG probe"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "arm-none-eabi-nm Projects/NUCLEO-L476RG/Examples/GPIO/BLINKY/STM32CubeIDE/Debug/BLINKY.elf | grep -E \"USART2_IRQHandler|Default_Handler|Infinite_Loop\"",
        "description": "List USART2/default handler symbols in the ELF"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "STM32_PROGRAMMER_DEFAULT_SN=066DFF485754727567021514 stm32 debug read-memory --address 0x080000D8 --size 4",
        "description": "Read USART2 vector table entry (IRQ 38)"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "arm-none-eabi-addr2line -f -e Projects/NUCLEO-L476RG/Examples/GPIO/BLINKY/STM32CubeIDE/Debug/BLINKY.elf 0x08002f54; arm-none-eabi-objdump -s -j .isr_vector Projects/NUCLEO-L476RG/Examples/GPIO/BLINKY/STM32CubeIDE/Debug/BLINKY.elf | sed -n '1,20p'",
        "description": "Map live handler address to ELF symbol and dump ELF static vector table"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "for elf in $(find Projects -name '*.elf' -path '*/Debug/*' 2>/dev/null); do sym=$(arm-none-eabi-nm \"$elf\" 2>/dev/null | grep -E ' [TtWw] USART2_IRQHandler$'); echo \"$elf -> $sym\"; done",
        "description": "Find USART2_IRQHandler address in every built ELF under Projects/"
      }
    }
  ],
  "final_text": "Multiple ST-LINK probes are attached \u2014 I need to pin the L476RG's probe serial:\n**Yes \u2014 the ISR is properly registered.** Here's the full picture:\n\n## Live vector table (read from the board)\n\n| What | Value |\n|---|---|\n| `SCB->VTOR` | `0x08000000` (table at flash base, not relocated) |\n| USART2 slot (`IRQ 38` \u2192 offset `0xD8`) | **`0x08002F55`** (thumb bit set \u2192 handler at `0x08002F54`) |\n\n## Symbol match\n\n`0x08002F54` resolves to **`T USART2_IRQHandler`** in `Projects/.../PWR/VCP-ECHO/STM32CubeIDE/Debug/VCP-ECHO.elf` \u2014 a **strong** text symbol, i.e. a real user-defined ISR, not the weak startup-file alias. So the vector entry points at a genuine handler, distinct from `Default_Handler`.\n\n## One caveat worth knowing\n\nThe board is **not running the descriptor's default firmware**. The descriptor resolves to `BLINKY.elf`, and in *that* image `USART2_IRQHandler` is still the weak alias for `Default_Handler` (`W` at `0x080014C4`, same address as `Infinite_Loop`) \u2014 its static vector slot holds `0x080014C5`. The flash contents instead match **VCP-ECHO** byte-for-byte at the USART2 slot.\n\nSo:\n- **What's flashed (VCP-ECHO):** USART2 ISR registered \u2705\n- **What the project descriptor points at (BLINKY):** still the default handler \u2014 but BLINKY never overrides it, which is expected for a GPIO blinky.\n\nIf you intended to be testing BLINKY, the bench has stale (VCP-ECHO) firmware on the L476RG and needs a reflash first."
}